This paper is primarily concerned with defining and measuring the intelligence of an artificial agent, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also makes use of concepts from computability theory (cs.LO) and information theory (cs.IT) to define the intelligence measure. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential limitations of intelligent machines, which could fall under the categories of computer security (cs.CR) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
